# Day 06 – Task Log

## Objective

To understand the fundamentals of CSS Grid and learn how to create structured and responsive layouts by organizing elements into rows and columns through practical implementation.

---

## Topics Covered

* Introduction to CSS Grid
* Grid Container and Grid Items
* `display: grid`
* `grid-template-columns`
* `grid-template-rows`
* `gap`
* `grid-column`
* `grid-row`
* Item Positioning in Grid Layouts
* Layout Replication Using CSS Grid

---

## Tasks Assigned

| Sr. No. | Task | File Name |
| ------: | ---------------------------------------------------- | ------------------- |
| 1 | Practice basic CSS Grid properties and item placement | `grid-practice.html` |
| 2 | Replicate the given layout using CSS Grid properties | `grid-layout.html` |

---

## Work Completed

Successfully practiced the fundamental concepts of CSS Grid by creating a basic grid layout and experimenting with rows, columns, spacing, and item positioning. After understanding the core properties, implemented a second project to replicate the grid design provided during the training session. These activities helped in gaining practical experience with modern layout techniques and understanding how complex webpage structures can be created using CSS Grid.

---

## Skills Practiced

* CSS3
* CSS Grid Layout
* Grid Container and Grid Items
* Layout Structuring
* Grid Positioning
* Responsive Design Concepts

---

## Learning Outcomes

* Understood the concept of grid containers and grid items.
* Learned how to create layouts using rows and columns.
* Gained practical experience in positioning elements within a grid.
* Learned how spacing and alignment work in CSS Grid.
* Improved the ability to replicate real-world layouts using modern CSS techniques.
* Developed a better understanding of structured webpage design.

---

## Challenges & Solutions

Initially found it difficult to determine the exact placement and sizing of grid items within the layout. By experimenting with different grid properties and creating a practice layout before replicating the assigned design, the concepts became easier to understand and implement.

---

## Conclusion

Today's session introduced the CSS Grid layout system through both practice exercises and a layout replication task. Working on these activities improved my understanding of grid-based layouts and strengthened my ability to create organized and responsive webpage structures using modern CSS techniques.




